🔷 What is JWT?

**JWT (JSON Web Token)** is a secure way to:

👉 Send user information between client & server

📌 Used for authentication

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Structure of JWT

A JWT has 3 parts:

```text id="h8k2p4"
Header.Payload.Signature
```

---

Example Token

```text id="k2p8m4"
eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 JWT Components

1️⃣ Header

```json id="p2k9m4"
{
  "alg": "HS256",
  "typ": "JWT"
}
```

---

2️⃣ Payload

```json id="m4k8p2"
{
  "userId": 123,
  "email": "user@example.com"
}
```

---

3️⃣ Signature

✔ Ensures token is secure
✔ Created using secret key

